 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"p4", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"Midpoint", "[", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"p3", ",", "p5"}], "}"}], "]"}]}], ";"}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9920971010732193`*^9, 3.992097111077364*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "In[303]:=",ExpressionUUID->"2cdf6675-e26c-41fa-b5d0-c00094b4f3fb"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "With all of our points now defined, we can begin calculating for the \
torque. The equation for torque is known as:\n\n\[Tau] = F*r*sin(\[Theta])\n\n\
If we assume the force to be gravitational force, then F = m * g.\n\nTo \
understand the torque exerted on our coordinate plane, we can go over an \
example with generic placeholders. Let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s say we have a point \
mass at (x,y) with mass m, distance r, and angle \[Theta] from the origin \
(0,0).\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  GraphicsBox[
   TagBox[RasterBox[CompressedData["
1:eJzs3Q18zXX/+PFzs1sz9/eGuVsh6QZR1IjEJaFLchO7KJRUUrlJa6Eu/qno
