       RowBox[{"thetaLean", ",", "0"}], "}"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"-", "90"}], ",", "90"}], "}"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"SaveDefinitions", "->", "True"}]}], "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.9925103126465883`*^9, {3.9925114567123623`*^9, 3.992511513890759*^9}, {
   3.9925115978278627`*^9, 3.99251160659545*^9}, {3.992511687526649*^9, 
   3.9925116894101353`*^9}, 3.992545447214129*^9, {3.992545604826027*^9, 
   3.992545613724739*^9}, 3.992547161441778*^9},
 CellLabel->
  "In[327]:=",ExpressionUUID->"6b49c801-9868-4090-96dd-9d23f2ef9136"],

Cell[BoxData[
 TagBox[
  StyleBox[
   DynamicModuleBox[{$CellContext`thetaLean$$ = 10, Typeset`show$$ = True, 
    Typeset`bookmarkList$$ = {}, Typeset`bookmarkMode$$ = "Menu", 
    Typeset`animator$$, Typeset`animvar$$ = 1, Typeset`name$$ = 
    "\"untitled\"", Typeset`specs$$ = {{{
       Hold[$CellContext`thetaLean$$], 0}, -90, 90, ControlType -> 
      Manipulator}}, Typeset`size$$ = {
    360., {177.134033203125, 182.865966796875}}, Typeset`update$$ = 0, 
    Typeset`initDone$$, Typeset`skipInitDone$$ = False, 
    Typeset`keyframeActionsQ$$ = False, Typeset`keyframeList$$ = {}}, 
    DynamicBox[Manipulate`ManipulateBoxes[
     1, StandardForm, "Variables" :> {$CellContext`thetaLean$$ = 0}, 
      "ControllerVariables" :> {}, 
      "OtherVariables" :> {
       Typeset`show$$, Typeset`bookmarkList$$, Typeset`bookmarkMode$$, 
        Typeset`animator$$, Typeset`animvar$$, Typeset`name$$, 
        Typeset`specs$$, Typeset`size$$, Typeset`update$$, Typeset`initDone$$,
         Typeset`skipInitDone$$, Typeset`keyframeActionsQ$$, 
        Typeset`keyframeList$$}, 
      "Body" :> $CellContext`drawMonkey2[$CellContext`thetaLean$$], 
      "Specifications" :> {{{$CellContext`thetaLean$$, 0}, -90, 90}}, 
      "Options" :> {}, "DefaultOptions" :> {}],
     ImageSizeCache->{409.1, {238.52454976111653`, 244.25648335486653`}},
     SingleEvaluation->True],
    Deinitialization:>None,
    DynamicModuleValues:>{},
    Initialization:>({$CellContext`drawMonkey2[
         Pattern[$CellContext`thetaLean, 
          Blank[]]] := 
       Module[{$CellContext`p1, $CellContext`p2, $CellContext`p3, \
$CellContext`p4, $CellContext`p5, $CellContext`p6, $CellContext`p5Visual, \
$CellContext`p4Visual, $CellContext`thetaAdjValue, $CellContext`dTailConst, \
$CellContext`output}, $CellContext`dTailConst = 
          5; $CellContext`p6 = {0, 
           0}; $CellContext`p2 = {(-$CellContext`hHead) 
            Sin[$CellContext`thetaLean Degree], $CellContext`hHead 
            Cos[$CellContext`thetaLean 
              Degree]}; $CellContext`p3 = {(-$CellContext`hTail) 
            Sin[$CellContext`thetaLean Degree], $CellContext`hTail 
            Cos[$CellContext`thetaLean Degree]}; $CellContext`p1 = {
           Part[$CellContext`p2, 1] - $CellContext`dHead 
            Cos[$CellContext`thetaLean Degree], 
            Part[$CellContext`p2, 2] - $CellContext`dHead 
            Sin[$CellContext`thetaLean Degree]}; $CellContext`p5 = {
           Part[$CellContext`p3, 1] + $CellContext`dTailConst 
             Cos[(90 + $CellContext`thetaLean - $CellContext`thetaAdj) 
               Degree], 
            Part[$CellContext`p3, 2] + $CellContext`dTailConst 
             Sin[(90 + $CellContext`thetaLean - $CellContext`thetaAdj) 
               Degree]}; $CellContext`p4 = 
          Midpoint[{$CellContext`p3, $CellContext`p5}]; \
$CellContext`objective = ($CellContext`torqueAtPoint[$CellContext`mTail, \
$CellContext`p4] + $CellContext`torqueAtPoint[$CellContext`mHead, \
$CellContext`p1])^2; $CellContext`constraints = 
          0 <= $CellContext`thetaAdj <= 360; $CellContext`output = Part[
            Part[
             
             NMinimize[{$CellContext`objective, $CellContext`constraints}, \
$CellContext`thetaAdj], 2], 1]; $CellContext`thetaAdjValue = 
          Values[$CellContext`output]; $CellContext`p5Visual = {
           Part[$CellContext`p3, 1] + $CellContext`dTailConst 
             Cos[(90 + $CellContext`thetaLean - $CellContext`thetaAdjValue) 
               Degree], 
            Part[$CellContext`p3, 2] + $CellContext`dTailConst 
             Sin[(90 + $CellContext`thetaLean - $CellContext`thetaAdjValue) 
               Degree]}; Graphics[{Blue, {
             Line[{$CellContext`p1, $CellContext`p2}], 
             Line[{$CellContext`p6, $CellContext`p3}], 
             Line[{$CellContext`p2, $CellContext`p3}], 
             Line[{$CellContext`p5Visual, $CellContext`p3}]}, LightGray, 
            Dashed, {
             Line[{{-10, 0}, {10, 0}}], 
             Line[{{0, -10}, {0, 10}}]}}, ImageSize -> Medium, 
           PlotRange -> {{-10, 10}, {-10, 10}}]], $CellContext`thetaLean$$ = 
       10, $CellContext`p1 = {-Cos[10 Degree] - 5 Sin[10 Degree], 
         5 Cos[10 Degree] - Sin[10 Degree]}, $CellContext`p2 = {(-5) 
         Sin[10 Degree], 5 Cos[10 Degree]}, $CellContext`p3 = {-
         Sin[10 Degree], 
         Cos[
         10 Degree]}, $CellContext`p4 = {(5 
           Cos[Degree (-100 + $CellContext`thetaAdj)])/2 - Sin[10 Degree], 
         Cos[10 Degree] + (5 Sin[Degree (-100 + $CellContext`thetaAdj)])/
          2}, $CellContext`p5 = {
        5 Cos[Degree (-100 + $CellContext`thetaAdj)] - Sin[10 Degree], 
         Cos[10 Degree] + 
         5 Sin[Degree (-100 + $CellContext`thetaAdj)]}, $CellContext`p6 = {0, 
        0}, $CellContext`p5Visual = {
        1.9999999999955058`, -3.582575694957801}, $CellContext`thetaAdjValue = 
       156.42182152185435`, $CellContext`dTailConst = 
       5, $CellContext`output = {
        3.8820022639629666`*^-25, {$CellContext`thetaAdj[1] -> 
          189.2916136663998, $CellContext`thetaAdj[2] -> 
          166.2526791890495, $CellContext`thetaAdj[3] -> 
          166.0983485132925, $CellContext`thetaAdj[4] -> 
          168.27015443995515`}}, $CellContext`hHead = 5, $CellContext`hTail = 
       1, $CellContext`dHead = 
       1, $CellContext`objective = (-
          Cos[10 Degree] + (5 Cos[Degree (-100 + $CellContext`thetaAdj)])/2 - 
         6 Sin[10 Degree])^2, $CellContext`torqueAtPoint[
         Pattern[$CellContext`mass, 
          Blank[]], 
         Pattern[$CellContext`coord, 
          Blank[]]] := 
       Module[{}, $CellContext`mass 
         Part[$CellContext`coord, 1]], $CellContext`mTail = 
       1, $CellContext`mHead = 1, $CellContext`constraints = 
       0 <= $CellContext`thetaAdj <= 360}; Typeset`initDone$$ = True),
    SynchronousInitialization->True,
    UndoTrackedVariables:>{Typeset`show$$, Typeset`bookmarkMode$$},
    UnsavedVariables:>{Typeset`initDone$$},
    UntrackedVariables:>{Typeset`size$$}], "Manipulate",
   Deployed->True,
   StripOnInput->False],
  Manipulate`InterpretManipulate[1]]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.992511459067482*^9, 3.9925114837484007`*^9}, {
   3.992511514280242*^9, 3.992511551824615*^9}, 3.99251160347538*^9, 
   3.992511690246126*^9, 3.992513099187531*^9, {3.992513159566625*^9, 
   3.992513161386998*^9}, {3.99254516043158*^9, 3.99254516205396*^9}, {
   3.992545393000306*^9, 3.9925454020667477`*^9}, {3.992545531986281*^9, 
   3.992545665010851*^9}, 3.9925457574175377`*^9, 3.9925458019185457`*^9, {
   3.9925471676690607`*^9, 3.992547184221044*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "Out[327]=",ExpressionUUID->"2f1c5fae-300c-4e80-b2e2-ad74186a8d86"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
Notice how there is several cases where the background becomes red, or there \
is NO SOLUTION to the problem. This is because you can only do so much with a \
single-jointed tail. To get around this, we develop a third model for a \
multi-jointed tail:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.992513170336986*^9, 
  3.9925132081499968`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b8014efa-9cc9-4c9e-972e-\
03107421f433"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Model V3 - Multi-Jointed Self-Balancing Tail", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.992100591446735*^9, {3.9921621171812067`*^9, 3.992162125037558*^9}, {
   3.992419485360118*^9, 3.992419489242263*^9}, {3.9924272718363523`*^9, 
   3.992427277888801*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"93d1465b-ed50-421e-9e24-\
077e0f67b308"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We now have a single-jointed tail which can rotate freely to counterbalance \
",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1acaeb06-1717-4e3e-ba3b-8fb87db7fc3f"],
 ". However, once again, in nature, monkeys and mammals in general have \
multi-jointed tails ranging from 11 to 49 caudal vertebrae (bones). To \
simulate this, we need to compute an algorithm that can take any number of \
joints, a given segment length and weight, and a ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b5da1eac-6ca5-459e-857f-cb812b0199f5"],
 ", and computes the angles of the vertebrae. \n\nTo do this, we need to \
redefine our naming system for our variables. Our system above has six \
points, each titled ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f11220db-5528-40e4-b7b1-ab3727f3427b"],
 ", but approaching adding more and more points as well as midpoints/center \
of masses computationally will get unnecessary and convoluted. Thus, for this \
final model, we will only name the pivot points with the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4a07840b-62d1-4cbf-8c24-a56b54ea56b7"],
 " system, and we will name midpoints/center of masses with the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c27c6d69-5bc1-4334-bcf5-6f1c447a524b"],
 " system. Because the n applies for the tail and only the tail, but we still \
have pivots and center of masses elsewhere, we will name the origin and head \
points with these special exceptions:\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "0"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "81739206-65a2-42a1-9495-88e5c4507fe3"],
 " - the origin\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "h"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1b6f197c-9565-4d2b-b894-eaede8a13027"],
 " - the pivot point of the head\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "h"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a4d2a068-6058-41c3-9397-01a752e3d7ed"],
 " - the point mass associated with the head.\n\nLet\[CloseCurlyQuote]s show \
an example of all of these rules in a diagram, in this case with 4 segments \
for the tail:\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  GraphicsBox[
